WEBVTT

00:00:00.196 --> 00:00:02.190
<v Lecturer>Okay, so now let's talk about</v>

00:00:02.190 --> 00:00:06.260
an exciting development which is called AWS Outposts.

00:00:06.260 --> 00:00:07.700
What is hybrid cloud?

00:00:07.700 --> 00:00:10.870
Businesses that keep an on-premise infrastructure

00:00:10.870 --> 00:00:12.840
alongside a cloud infrastructure

00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:14.963
are called hybrid cloud.

00:00:16.141 --> 00:00:17.130
And when we have that,

00:00:17.130 --> 00:00:20.130
we have two ways of dealing with IT systems.

00:00:20.130 --> 00:00:23.610
We have one for the cloud of AWS, for example

00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:26.420
using the console of AWS, the CLI

00:00:26.420 --> 00:00:29.000
and the APIs from AWS,

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:30.840
but also we have another one

00:00:30.840 --> 00:00:34.100
that is dedicated to on-premises infrastructure.

00:00:34.100 --> 00:00:36.750
And so, that means two different types of skillsets,

00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:37.830
two different types of API,

00:00:37.830 --> 00:00:40.030
and that may be complicated.

00:00:40.030 --> 00:00:42.270
So it was said, "Okay, we do recognize

00:00:42.270 --> 00:00:44.730
that some companies will run a hybrid cloud

00:00:44.730 --> 00:00:47.330
therefore, let's create Outpost."

00:00:47.330 --> 00:00:49.150
And Outpost our server racks

00:00:49.150 --> 00:00:51.610
that offer the same AWS infrastructure,

00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:53.400
services, API and tools

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:56.060
to build your own application on-premises

00:00:56.060 --> 00:00:57.540
just like in the cloud.

00:00:57.540 --> 00:00:58.720
So what this means is that

00:00:58.720 --> 00:01:00.680
they will come and set up

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:04.290
and manage Outpost racks which are servers

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:06.620
within your on premises infrastructure.

00:01:06.620 --> 00:01:09.370
And then these servers come preloaded

00:01:09.370 --> 00:01:11.340
with the (indistinct) services

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:13.710
but you can benefit them from on-premises.

00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.150
So as we can see now on your corporate data center

00:01:16.150 --> 00:01:20.170
you will have your Outpost racks directly set up by AWS.

00:01:20.170 --> 00:01:22.370
And this allows you to extend

00:01:22.370 --> 00:01:24.500
the (indistinct) services directly

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:26.390
onto your on-premises data centers

00:01:26.390 --> 00:01:28.680
which is I think revolutionary.

00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:31.020
But a difference between an EC2 instance

00:01:31.020 --> 00:01:32.010
running on the cloud

00:01:32.010 --> 00:01:34.570
and an EC2 instance running in your own data center

00:01:34.570 --> 00:01:38.340
is that now you are responsible for their security,

00:01:38.340 --> 00:01:41.180
the physical security of the rack itself

00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:44.133
because that rack is within your own data center.

00:01:45.550 --> 00:01:47.860
The benefits from using Outposts are many,

00:01:47.860 --> 00:01:49.960
first of all, you get low latency access

00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:51.590
to on-premise the system,

00:01:51.590 --> 00:01:52.970
you get local data processing

00:01:52.970 --> 00:01:56.410
so the data may actually never leave your on-premise system

00:01:56.410 --> 00:01:57.810
and never go to the cloud,

00:01:57.810 --> 00:01:59.390
data residency, so again, it lives

00:01:59.390 --> 00:02:00.980
within your own data centers.

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:03.290
It's easy for example, to start the migration

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:05.420
from on-premise is to Outpost

00:02:05.420 --> 00:02:08.230
and then when you're ready from Outpost to the cloud.

00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:09.260
It's a fully managed service.

00:02:09.260 --> 00:02:11.680
So AWS will manage the service for you.

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:13.480
And with Outpost for now,

00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:15.630
you can launch a lot of services

00:02:15.630 --> 00:02:19.700
such as Amazon EC2, Amazon EBS, Amazon S3

00:02:19.700 --> 00:02:24.700
Amazon EKS, Amazon ECS, Amazon RDS, and Amazon EMR.

00:02:24.800 --> 00:02:28.190
So it's really a cool way to extend the cloud directly

00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:32.450
onto your own our infrastructure on-premises system,

00:02:32.450 --> 00:02:33.700
and this is revolutionary.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:35.260
So this may come up in the exam.

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:36.093
I hope you liked it.

00:02:36.093 --> 00:02:38.020
And I will see you in the next lecture.